Third-party archived materials
================================

This directory holds one-time, legally redistributable research materials used to
enrich country pages. The repository's root MIT license applies to project code
and curated site text. Upstream materials remain under their own terms below.

U.S. State Department — International Religious Freedom (IRF) reports
---------------------------------------------------------------------
Location: state_dept/
Status: U.S. government works are not subject to U.S. copyright
        (17 U.S.C. §105). State Department policy permits copying and
        distribution of unmarked content. Citation appreciated.
        Do not redistribute third-party photos/graphics that may be copyrighted.
Source: https://www.state.gov/international-religious-freedom-reports/

U.S. Commission on International Religious Freedom (USCIRF)
------------------------------------------------------------
Location: uscirf/
Status: Federal commission reports prepared as U.S. government works;
        no U.S. copyright in staff-produced report text under 17 U.S.C. §105.
        Attribution to USCIRF is recommended.
Source: https://www.uscirf.gov/publications/uscirf-annual-report

